      "comment": "MISS BEAR (1) has a strong record this journey with three wins and a minor from five starts. Scored by 4.5 lengths last time (25.42) in a Grade 4/5 over 457m at Q Lakeside. Looks the one to beat with even luck. GRACE ILE (6) took the sit on the lead from an outside box but levelled up and drew clear to score (25.51) at Q Lakeside in Grade 5 over 457m. Comes out of a solid form race last start. Hard to fault recent form and looks a key chance again. ZIPPING CHEBET (2) lit up the clock in 19.68 when winning a Grade 5 over 366m at Capalaba last start. Rates a leading chance if runs up to latest. RITZA LAW (7) is always hard to beat when he races at this trip.",
